 SpaceX, xAI, and X Holdings. The filing states only at a general level that all such historical related party transactions between the entities have been eliminated in consolidation as part of the common-control accounting. The specific dollar amounts disclosed in the related party transactions section pertain to dealings with **Tesla** and **The Boring Company**, which are related parties but remain **outside** the consolidated group and therefore are not subject to elimination. To identify the specific quantified intercompany flows among SpaceX, xAI, and X, one would likely need to consult the full consolidated financial statement notes (particularly any segment reporting or revenue disaggregation notes) that may provide more granular detail on intercompany activity prior to elimination.',
