        output='# Analysis of Related Party Transactions Note\n\n## Important Finding\n\nBased on the chunks provided, **the filing does not enumerate specific pre-merger intercompany transactions between SpaceX, xAI, and X Holdings that were eliminated in consolidation.** The disclosure is limited to a general statement:\n\n> "all historical related party transactions between the entities have been eliminated in consolidation"\n\nThe detailed "Related Party Transactions" note that follows focuses almost exclusively on transactions with **external** affiliated parties — primarily Tesla, The Boring Company, Musk-owned entities, and Valor Equity Partners — not on intercompany dealings among SpaceX, xAI, and X themselves.\n\n## Responses to Your Five Specific Questions\n\n### (1) xAI providing AI services or compute to X Holdings pre-X Merger\n**Not found.** While the prospectus discusses Grok\'s integration with X (approximately 117 million MAUs using Grok\'s AI features as of March 31, 2026), this is described as a post-merger strategic benefit, not as a disclosed pre-merger related party transaction with quantified amounts.\n\n### (2) X Holdings providing data or platform services to xAI pre-X Merger\n**Not found.** The filing describes X\'s real-time data as a competitive differentiator for Grok ("Grok\'s deep integration with X enables freshness, relevance, and contextual awareness"), but this is presented as strategic narrative, not as a disclosed related party transaction with associated financial amounts that would have been eliminated.\n\n### (3) SpaceX providing launch services or Starlink services to xAI or X Holdings\n**Not found.** None of the provided chunks mention SpaceX supplying launch, Starlink broadband, or Starlink Mobile services to xAI or X as intercompany transactions. The SpaceX-Tesla commercial agreements are detailed (SpaceX obtained goods/services of $11M in 2023, $4M in 2024, $144M in 2025), but no equivalent disclosure exists for SpaceX-xA