llowing the consummation of" the merger.\n\n### Transactions with Elon Musk and Affiliated Entities\n\n**Mr. Musk\'s affiliations**: Founder, CEO, CTO, Chairman of SpaceX; "Technoking," CEO, and director of Tesla (~20% shareholder as of November 10, 2025); founder of The Boring Company; was stockholder, director, and officer of xAI and X prior to the mergers.\n\n**Tesla\'s SpaceX ownership**: Beneficial owner of 18,990,195 Class A shares as of May 1, 2026 — less than 1.0% of total outstanding after the offering.\n\n**SpaceX–Tesla commercial, licensing and support agreements** (goods/services obtained by SpaceX):\n| Period | Amount |\n|---|---|\n| 2023 | $11 million |\n| 2024 | $4 million |\n| 2025 | $144 million |\n| Jan 1–Feb 28, 2026 | $0.2 million |\n\n**xAI–Tesla commercial, licensing and support agreements** (goods/services obtained by xAI):\n| Period | Amount Obtained | Revenue Recognized by xAI |\n|---|---|---|\n| 2024 | $191 million | — |\n| 2025 | $506 million | $2 million |\n| Jan 1–Feb 28, 2026 | $34 million | $0.4 million |\n\n**X Holdings–Tesla advertising agreements** (Tesla advertising on X):\n| Period | Amount |\n|---|---|\n| 2024 | $0.5 million |\n| 2025 | $4 million |\n| Jan 1–Feb 28, 2026 | $0 |\n\n**Aircraft usage** (SpaceX charging Tesla for aircraft use by Musk and Tesla personnel):\n| Period | Amount Charged |\n|---|---|\n| 2023 | $1 million |\n| 2024 | $1 million |\n| 2025 | $2 million |\n| Jan 1–Feb 28, 2026 | $0 |\n\n**X–Boring Company office lease** (X leasing from a Boring Company subsidiary):\n| Period | Lease Payments |\n|---|---|\n| 2024 | $0.1 million |\n| 2025 | $1 million |\n| Jan 1–Feb 28, 2026 | $0.1 million |\n\n**SpaceX–Boring Company tunnel construction**: SpaceX incurred $1 million in 2025 for tunnel construction by The Boring Company in Bastrop, Texas.\n\n**xAI–Musk Industries LLC real property lease**:\n| Period | Lease Payments |\n|---|---|\n| 2024 | $0.5 million |\n| 2025 | $2 million |\n| Jan 1–Feb 28, 2026 | $0.2 million |\n\n**SpaceX–Musk security company** (security services for Mr. Musk):\n| Period | Expenses |\n|---|---|\n| 2023 | $2 million |\n| 2024 | $3 million |\n| 2025 | $4 million |\n| Jan 1–Feb 28, 2026 | $1 million |\n\n### Transactions with Antonio J. Gracias and Valor Equity Partners\n\nMr. Gracias is a board member and founder/CEO/CIO of Valor Equity Partners.\n\n**xAI–Valor equipment leases** (three separate computing equipment lease agreements):\n\n| Lease | Aggregate Cash Payments Over Lease Life |\n|---|---|\n| Lease 1 | $6,986 million |\n| Lease 2 | $6,633 million |\n| Lease 3 | $6,587 million |\n| **Total** | **$20,206 million** |\n\nLessee payments and performance obligations are guaranteed by Space Exploration Technologies Corp. or one of its subsidiaries.\n\nPayments made under these leases:\n| Period | Amount |\n|---|---|\n| 2025 | $885 million |\n| Jan 1–Feb 28, 2026 | $857 million |\n\n**Valor Transaction II**: Deemed a failed sale-leaseback transaction; the Company recorded related debt of $5,365 million.\n\n**X–Valor API services** (X received payments from Valor):\n| Period | Amount |\n|---|---|\n| 2024 | $1 million |\n| 2025 | $1 million |\n| Jan 1–Feb 28, 2026 | $0.1 million |\n\n### Other Transactions with Directors and Executive Officers\n\nSpaceX owns and operates, through subsidiary Falcon Landing, LLC, three aircraft for use by directors, executive officers, and others. (The chunk cuts off here in the provided text.)\n\n### xAI Merger Consideration\n\nOn February 2, 2026, SpaceX issued (pre-2026 Stock Split):\n- 321.7 million shares of Class A Common Stock\n- 121.7 million shares of Class B Common Stock\n- $2,947 million in cash\n\n...to holders of xAI Common Stock and Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock.\n\n### Tesla\'s xAI Investment and SpaceX Class A Issuance\n\n- January 2026: Tesla agreed to invest $2,000 million in xAI Series E Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock\n- Conditioned on regulatory approvals\n- Post-xAI Merger: Tesla\'s right converted into right to acquire SpaceX Class A common stock\n- March 12, 2026: SpaceX issued 3.8 million Class A shares (pre-split basis) to Tesla\n\n---\n\n## Key Takeaway\n\nThe filing\'s approach to the eliminated intercompany transactions is notably **non-specific**. While it states that "all historical related party transactions between the entities have been eliminated in consolidation," it does **not** enumerate what those transactions were, their nature, or their dollar amounts. This is consistent with standard accounting practice for common-control combinations — ASC 805-50 requires elimination of intercompany balances and transactions but does not require separate disclosure of each eliminated item. The detailed related party disclosures that follow focus on transactions with **external** related parties (Tesla, Boring Company, Valor, Musk-owned entities) that survive consolidation because they involve parties outside the SpaceX-xAI-X corporate family.\n\nThe absence of specific intercompany transaction disclosures means that based on the provided chunks, **none of your five categories of pre-merger intercompany transactions are specifically identified** in the filing.',
