sclosures regarding intersegment pricing or transfer pricing methodologies. The only disclosure regarding intersegment financial interactions is the explicit statement that no inter-segment revenue is recognized for internal Starlink launches, as quoted in point (1): *"the Company does not recognize any inter-segment revenue..."*\n\n**(4) Disclosure about how the segments interact commercially**\nThe filing describes the segments as a "vertically integrated innovation engine" where the Space segment provides foundational infrastructure (launch capacity and satellites) that enables the Connectivity and AI segments to operate and grow. The exact language detailing these commercial interactions includes:\n> "We have three reportable segments in our vertically integrated innovation engine: Space, Connectivity, and AI. In our Space segment, we design, manufacture, and launch reusable rockets to provide high cadence, reliable, and affordable access to space at unprecedented scale. In our Connectivity segment, we operate a worldwide high-speed, low-latency broadband data and communications network powered by over 9,600 Starlink broadband and mobile satellites in Low-Earth Orbit, delivering connectivity to millions of consumer, enterprise, and government customers across 164 countries, territories, and other markets. In our AI segment, we operate a highly vertically integrated AI platform spanning our truth-seeking frontier model Grok, AI solutions for consumer and enterprise customers, X—our real-time information, entertainment, and free speech platform—and AI computational infrastructure."\n\nAdditionally, the filing details a future commercial interaction where the Connectivity segment (via Starlink) will support the AI segment\'s orbital compute infrastructure:\n> "...satellites in Sun-synchronous orbit will be able to handle energy-intensive AI workloads, such as inference demand, at far greater scale and efficiency than terrestrial alternatives, with Starlink providing low-latency, global connectivity linking these orbital AI systems to people around the world and delivering real-time intelligence. We expect to begin deploying our orbital AI compute satellites as early as 2028."\n\nAnd, as noted in point (2), the Space segment is described as providing foundational strategic value to the other two segments:\n> "...its financial results do not reflect the foundational strategic value that it provides to us in bolstering the growth of our Connectivity and AI segments."',
