tween the entities have been eliminated in consolidation." Therefore, any historical intercompany revenue (such as from X to xAI) is eliminated and not recognized as external revenue in the consolidated financial statements.\n*   **Related Party Revenue from External Parties:** The only disclosed related-party revenue from external entities involving X or xAI comes from **Tesla**:\n    *   **xAI commercial, licensing, and support agreements:** xAI recognized revenue of $2 million in 2025 and $0.4 million from January 1, 2026 through February 28, 2026 from Tesla.\n    *   **X Holdings advertising agreements:** Tesla purchased advertising on the X platform totaling $0.5 million in 2024, $4 million in 2025, and $0 from January 1, 2026 through February 28, 2026.\n\n### 3. Revenue Disaggregation Note\nRevenue is disaggregated by type and segment across three segments: Space, Connectivity, and AI. \n\n**For the Year Ended December 31, 2025:**\n*   **Space Segment:** $4,086 million (Launch Services: $2,576 million; Launch & Development: $1,510 million)\n*   **Connectivity Segment:** $11,387 million (Consumer: $7,208 million; Enterprise & Government: $4,179 million)\n*   **AI Segment:** $3,201 million (Advertising: $1,844 million; AI Solutions & Infrastructure: $1,357 million)\n*   **Total Revenues:** $18,674 million\n\n**For the Three Months Ended March 31, 2026:**\n*   **Space Segment:** $619 million (Launch Services: $330 million; Launch & Development: $289 million)\n*   **Connectivity Segment:** $3,257 million (Consumer: $2,148 million; Enterprise & Government: $1,109 million)\n*   **AI Segment:** $818 million (Advertising: $343 million; AI Solutions & Infrastructure: $475 million)\n*   **Total Revenues:** $4,694 million\n\n*(Note: All product revenue is attributable solely to the Connectivity segment).*',
