ents.\n\n---\n\n## (3) All-Stock Nature of the X Merger and Prior Commercial Relationships\n\n**All-stock nature — confirmed.** As quoted above:\n\n> "The Mergers were each effected through a share exchange."\n\nAnd the specific X Merger ratio:\n\n> "each class of common stock of X Holdings Corp. ("X Common Stock") was converted to 2.776 shares of xAI Common Stock of the same class"\n\n**Suggestion of prior commercial relationships — not explicitly found.** The text does not frame the X Merger as formalizing or consolidating pre-existing commercial arrangements between xAI and X. The rationale given for the mergers is framed around common control and strategic integration, not prior commercial ties:\n\n> "The Mergers have been accounted for as reorganizations of entities under common control as Mr. Elon Musk had a controlling financial interest in the Company, xAI and X through his majority voting interest in each such entity during the periods presented in these consolidated financial statements."\n\nThe only indirect acknowledgment that inter-entity transactions existed is the elimination language:\n\n> "all historical related party transactions between the entities have been eliminated in consolidation"\n\n---\n\n## (4) X\'s Advertising, Subscription, or Data Licensing Revenue Recognition Before vs. After the Merger\n\n**Current revenue recognition policies — found, but no before/after comparison.** The text describes the company\'s current policies:\n\n> "The Company generates revenue from (i) the sale of ad products displayed on its X platform, and (ii) providing AI solutions and infrastructure, which includes subscription-related offerings, data licensing arrangements, and API"\n\nFor advertising:\n\n> "Revenue for advertising services is recognized in the period when advertising is delivered as evidenced by a person engaging with an ad on the Company\'s platforms in a manner satisfying the types of engagement selected by the advertisers. The Company\'s contract terms for advertising services are typically cancellable short-term arrangements."\n\nFor subscriptions and data licensing:\n\n> "Revenue for AI solutions and infrastructure includes: (i) premium subscriptions on X and Grok which is recognized ratably over the period of the subscription term (ranging from month-to-month to one year), (ii) data licensing revenue which is generally recognized ratably over the period (from month-to-month to two years) in which the"\n\n**No disclosure was found** comparing how X\'s revenue recognition differed before versus after the merger. The text presents these as the company\'s current policies without distinguishing pre-merger X practices.\n\n---\n\n## (5) Intercompany Services Between SpaceX and xAI or X\n\n**General elimination statement — found; specific services — not found.** The only disclosure is the blanket statement:\n\n> "all historical related party transactions between the entities have been eliminated in consolidation"\n\nThe Related Party Transactions section focuses on transactions with **Tesla** and **The Boring Company** — entities outside the SpaceX/xAI/X consolidated group. Specific examples found include:\n\n- **SpaceX–Tesla commercial agreements:** "we obtained goods and services of $11 million in 2023, $4 million in 2024, $144 million in 2025, and $0.2 million from January 1, 2026 through February 28"\n- **xAI–Tesla commercial agreements:** "xAI obtained goods and services of $191 million in 2024, $506 million in 2025, and $34 million from January 1, 2026 through February 28, 2026"\n- **X–Tesla advertising:** "Tesla has directly and indirectly purchased advertising on our X platform. These amounts totaled $0.5 million in 2024, $4 million in 2025, and $0 from January 1, 2026 through"\n- **Aircraft usage with Tesla:** "we charged Tesla $1 million in 2023, $1 million in 2024, $2 million in 2025, and $0 from January 1, 2026 through February 28"\n- **X–Boring Company lease:** "In 2024, X entered into a lease for office space with a subsidiary owned by The Boring Company"\n\n**No specific disclosure** was found itemizing intercompany services rendered between SpaceX and xAI, or between SpaceX and X, either before or after the mergers. The text confirms such transactions existed (via the elimination language) but does not describe their nature or amounts.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Item | Found? |\n|------|--------|\n| (1) X Merger consideration | **Yes** — 2.776 xAI shares per X share, via share exchange |\n| (1) Pre-merger xAI–X commercial agreements | **No** — only generic elimination language |\n| (2) Grok licensed to X / X data to xAI pre-merger | **No** — only post-merger integration described |\n| (3) All-stock nature confirmed | **Yes** — "share exchange" |\n| (3) Suggestion of prior commercial relationships | **No** — framed as common-control reorganization |\n| (4) Revenue recognition before vs. after merger | **No** — current policies described, no comparison |\n| (5) Intercompany services SpaceX↔xAI/X | **No** — only generic elimination; specifics limited to Tesla/Boring Company |',
